decks.notes: The main concept of this deck is to control the game through the use of enchantments. The deck focuses on generating mana with cards like Sanctum Weaver and Utopia Sprawl, while also drawing cards with Sythis, Harvest's Hand and Enchantress's Presence. It uses cards like Destiny Spinner and March of Otherworldly Light to protect itself and disrupt the opponent's strategy. The deck also includes a mix of removal and disruption with cards like On Thin Ice and Blood Moon. It aims to create a lock on the game with Solitary Confinement and win through attrition.

Utilizing a variety of removal spells, counterspells, and disruptive creatures, this deck aims to control the game and out-value the opponent by efficiently dealing with threats and maintaining card advantage. The deck's mana base allows for flexibility and consistency in casting its spells, while cards like Cling to Dust provide additional resources and resilience against graveyard strategies. With a focus on disruption and tempo, this BUG Control deck seeks to dominate the battlefield and dictate the pace of the game against a wide range of opponents in the Modern format.
